<br>
Hearing the noise behind me, I panic - searching<br>
left and right - hurrying - racing away - from what or whom I dare not speak - I could only gasp a scream back into my throat...... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/bvoiceofthedragon.showUserPublicProfile?gid=linamas>Linamas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Shardwurm</span><br>  Posts: 103<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(11/15/02 8:21:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/fvoiceofthedragonfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Whispering (roleplay)</span><hr size=1> Wandering aimlessly through the area, I see a shadow slip behind a tree.  I halt in the moonlight, searching for a place to hide.  She saw me, she had to have.  I look down at my armor, shining brightly in the moonlight.  What am I to do?  I breathlessly creep to a nearby shrub, and there I wait, hidden from view.  Only a slight gleam from my sword reveals my presence.<br>
<br>
The damp grass is brushing against my face, testing my every capability to hide.  As I watch the trees, I see without a doubt the slim shape begin to slip in and out of vision...<br>
<br>
The figure startles, from what I know not.  She begins to flee silently into the east.  What startled her? Protect her, I must...<br>
<br>
As I begin my search of her hiding place the silence is broken by an ear splitting screech that rips through the night followed by a Whisper that can only be made by one creature... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/bvoiceofthedragon.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dureln>Dureln</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Green Snake</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(11/15/02 10:20:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/fvoiceofthedragonfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Whispering (roleplay)</span><hr size=1> I materialize atop of the ancient spires in the dark dense forest, following rumors of a nameless fear.  In an effort to combat the malevolent darkness, I conjure a halo of light.  As it radiates from in my hand, it pierces the darkness to revile countless demons surrounding me!! I startle!! And then realize that they are only the shadows of the trees.  I take a breath of relief.<br>
<br>
But then, I hear a gasp, and a rustle of underbrush from behind me!  My familiar Yaps and dives under the confines of my robes for protection as i snap around to catch a glimpse of what was there only to find more shadows.<br>
<br>
Again in nearly the same area I hear another rustle in the foliage and from within the forest a gleam of steel reflecting the light of my halo can be seen.  Someone is there.  And they're armed.  In Panic!! I channel from within me all the arcane powers and prepare to unleash the most devastating blast a wizard of my caliber can bear to destroy the intruder!!  BUT!! My concentration is broken by a terrifying cry emanating from the other end of the forest.  It cuts through my heart as a knife through soft butter.  It is that for which I came.  The rumors are true.  Something IS here.<br>
<br>
I am petrified with fear.  Then I hear a voice whisper to me and I have no other choice than to listen...<br>
