 <br>
   ..I was a child of Kelethin....the youngest of four boys to a father who was cold...angry...and a drunkard.  Ne'er was there a time when he did not have an ale in his hand.  He would come home from the Tavern late at night-and as was normal, angry.  And he lashed out..violently..he would sting the child with words, and with hands, and with whips or belts..I could not do anything to stop it.  Mother tried to soften the blows with kind words later, but the pain ne'er did leave.  I ne'er knew a kind word from him, and the gentle touch of Love from him was as alien as our Dark Brethren of Neriak.  <br>
 <br>
  I tried...I made my way through schooling...excelling in Elven Historical Studies...Vocal Stylings...Norrathian Geography...none of it pleased him.  I acted in plays, surpassed anything anyone in the family had done...nothing was sufficient.  All I ever wanted was to make him proud of me....<br>
 <br>
   He killed himself with drink.  The doctor didst say his body gave out.  And at his burial I sang a hymn to Tunare.<br>
   Shortly thereafter, my mother's light expired.  Though he was often cruel to me, he loved her, and she died of a broken heart.  And at her burial I sang a hymn to Tunare.<br>
 <br>
  <br>
      My brothers scattered.  To where I know not.  I took up the lessons of Maesyn and learned the ways of the Faydark Champions.  When I was of age, I ventured into the Faydark to do battle..first with the Orcs, and then anything which threatened me.  I took risks some people might not otherwise, for I do not fear.  Not for mineself.<br>
 <br>
   My name is Peraspera Adastra.  It means Through the Thorns, To the Stars.  A looser translation would be go through Hell to reach the Promised Land.<br>
 I have been through Hell.  And Im seeking that Star.<br>
 I fight a life against a Ghost who hits me still.<br>
 I strive with everything within my Soul to please a man dead 6 long years.<br>
 I fight against a Ghost that only I can see.<br>
 <br>
 <br>
 ...All I e'er wanted was to make thee proud, Father..Why must you hit me?  No daddy, no............<br>
 <br>
 <br>
 <br>
  <br>
  ...a frightened scream breaks me from mine somber reminiscance.  A young elf in trouble from the horrors which abound here at night.  I raise my sword in Defiance to join the fray.....<br>
 <br>
  ..Put the Ghost away for now, Pera...He'll be back soon enough, but for now, keep thy mind on the task at hand.  Somebody needs help. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/bvoiceofthedragon.showUserPublicProfile?gid=selicatiren@voiceofthedragon>Selicatiren</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Green Snake</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(12/23/02 12:41:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/fvoiceofthedragonfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> My Rescuer</span><hr size=1> His sword slashes towards me and terrified I scream. What is that! an arrow through the goblin's chest? I look around and in the darkness of High Hold Keep I see my rescuer-Peraspera.<br>
On bended knee, I thank him, yet he lets me stay kneeling not. He praises me with a &quot;My Lady&quot; and I turn BRIGHT red. I am no lady, as he would know if my past were not such a secret.<br>
My past! Alas, It cannot be undone. The lack of wealth, the servitude, the pain and anguish.....<br>
I will not remines though For I have vowed to avenge the deaths, and to find any survivers that remain. My family, my friends, they will not regret that they saved me. And so I continue to fight... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/bvoiceofthedragon.showUserPublicProfile?gid=watchyurbb>WatchyurBB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Green Snake</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(12/24/02 6:17:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/fvoiceofthedragonfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My Rescuer</span><hr size=1> As I watch the candle slowly flicker down to its death while listening to the listless barkeep wipe down the bar with the same filthy rag he's been using for the last six months. I can't help but think that I need to stop hanging out in this run down shadowhaven bar. But my memmories always draw me back. Memmories of her, her soft laugh her soft voice The playfull way she would nuke me instead of the mob. INNKEEP!!! fill me another dirty glass and pass me that bowl of batwing crunchies  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/bvoiceofthedragon.showUserPublicProfile?gid=selicatiren@voiceofthedragon>Selicatiren</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Green Snake</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(12/25/02 1:46:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/fvoiceofthedragonfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> UGH, Why did I eat the worms?</span><hr size=1> From Highhold I traveled, following a kitty, but we often had to stop. UGH, those worms... If I had known that the inn was just over the hill, I wouldn't have eaten them, but now I'm stuck. I'll stay in this inn and drink till the pain in my gut leaves. The kitty needed to rest anyway, and he is gonna take a bath if I have any say. I don't care how much he claims he's supposed to be GREY, I know he used to be WHITE... oh well, I guess I'll call it a night... Barkeep, give me another, and tell me the gossip about the traveling people, then I'll go on to bed... TOTER! YOU saw him! WHERE? I must be reunited with my Brother! An extra tip to you if you tell me all you know... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/bvoiceofthedragon.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sonjaleah>Sonjaleah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Goddess of Scale</span><br>  Posts: 187<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(12/25/02 4:28:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/fvoiceofthedragonfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Whispering (roleplay)</span><hr size=1> My body tightens - my face drawn into a frown I look into the clouds - worried for the pain I see ahead.  Raising my hands palms outstretched I chant the ancient words - power begins to flow through me. I call unto the night.<br>
<br>
Why has this happen - alone because I play in bed with the dark one? because...because they really see what is underneath?<br>
<br>
....concentrating harder the wind pulls at my dress scattering my hair in all directions - I begin to turn - my eyes turn black........around and around till...falling to my knees - grabbing at my throat as if someone was strangling me ....all that is heard is my scream - gasping &quot;HOW CAN THIS BE&quot;!<br>
<br>
Rising to my feet I run through the forest paying no mind to my friends as I cross them on the path.  Tears streaming down my cheeks.  Arriving at my home I throw open the doors - hurrying down the hall to the warm fire awaiting..I then crumble - my mind fragmented - the only sound other than the crackle of the burning wood is my tears crying out...alone alone alone alone...... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/bvoiceofthedragon.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sonjaleah>Sonjaleah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Goddess of Scale</span><br>  Posts: 189<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(12/27/02 3:13:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/fvoiceofthedragonfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Whispering (roleplay)</span><hr size=1> Morning light streams in from the window above my bed.  Dancingly it teases my eyes as I awake.  Remembering the nights sorrows and the many bottles of wine - I cover my head with my silken pillow.<br>
<br>
Mummering....Ugg get out of bed - you lazy woman - things to be done - our house to make ready.  The Dragons are coming....why in the world do I worry about being alone when I am aways surrounded with my friends.  <br>
<br>
Swinging my legs over the side of the bed..my feet touch the cold floor.  To lost in my thoughts to notice the sleeping form beside me rolls over - eyes watching me quietly.<br>
<br>
Dropping my pillow and blanket covering me - I tiptoe naked across the cold floor to my closet. <br>
<br>
Hmmm now what to wear......<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/bvoiceofthedragon.showUserPublicProfile?gid=peraspera@voiceofthedragon>Peraspera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Green Snake</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(12/28/02 1:41:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/fvoiceofthedragonfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> the morning</span><hr size=1>   <br>
   The morning woke painfully.  Dreadfully so.<br>
 <br>
 Light streaming in through a window..hurting his eyes.<br>
 He shut them tightly, trying to hide from the pain..from<br>
 the memories...<br>
 <br>
  He had done something he did not ever do.  He had<br>
 imbibed ale.  And a lot of it..  It was always tough this<br>
 time of year to block out the memories which haunted<br>
 him.  So he chose to drown them this night instead.<br>
 <br>
   ..he had vague recollections of the night.  A lot of drinks.  Sitting quietly in a corner booth, drowning any conscious thoughts he might have otherwise had.  And there was a woman...He could barely remember..All a blur..everything so foggy.....<br>
 <br>
 <br>
   And thats when he took notice of where he was.<br>
 He was in a bed.  And it was not his.  Nay, he had not seen his own bed in months.  The rustling sound next to him jogged his memory...he had taken her home.  What may or may not have happened was lost to the night.<br>
 <br>
 <br>
  He watched her walk across the room nude.<br>
 <br>
  Why, Tunare, Why?  I have shamed this poor woman.<br>
 I have taken advantage of the situation.  Or was it I who was taken advantage of?  So much ale...so little thought...so much light.....so very naked. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/bvoiceofthedragon.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whispurrwillowind>WhispurrWillowind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Green Snake</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(12/30/02 7:16:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/fvoiceofthedragonfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The elusive toes...</span><hr size=1> We were all in the Great Divide, Watchyur, Deknyr, Darksider and a few more friends, hunting giants for their elusive toes.  Not the normal kind I must say, but the painted ones, as described by Deknyr (we were told he has something for painted toes).  <br>
<br>
After searching without success, we started to think that maybe the  giants were all afflicted with frostbite and their toes fell off.  It was only after tremendous bravery and unrelentless perseverance that we were able to salvage a few toes for Dek's collection.  <br>
<br>
Later on in the night, during a snow storm, Peraspera joined us and offered assistance in helping us with a frontal attack of the fort.  He seemed troubled in some way, his mind elsewhere.  Unfortunately, we were all plagued with fatigue and exaustion from the earlier battles and opted for an early port to Nexus.  <br>
<br>
Deknyr went back home with his treasure of toes. Watchyur made a quick stop to the Shadow Heaven bar and I tagged along, tired, weary but ready for a cold one.<br>
<br>
I was told that Peraspera went back to the frozen land to hunt Walruses in solitude.  May Tunare bless him with courage and peace.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/bvoiceofthedragon.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whispurrwillowind>WhispurrWillowind</A> at: 12/30/02 8:45:51 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/bvoiceofthedragon.showUserPublicProfile?gid=selicatiren@voiceofthedragon>Selicatiren</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Green Snake</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(12/30/02 11:26:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/fvoiceofthedragonfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> On the trail I continue</span><hr size=1>    What I learned from the barkeep I shall remember for some time. My brother Toter has been taken against his will to the Plane of Hate. However I am still no match for the beasts there. To find my brother I must find a group of six allies and search again on this trail. I wonder who in this inn would help me? Do I have to go to another place to find aid? and what about that kitty? why did he leave me to pay the bill on my own? <br>
   Also... Where did that ranger that once helped me go? His name I barely remember. It was... Per..aspera...Ad.......astra! Peraspera Adastra! Where did he go? I had assumed that he would help me, though I suppose I might have received aid had I not been drunk, and had I not neglected to tell him why I quest on.<br>
   Oh well, I believe that I shall go back to the ruins of my once prosperous home in Kelethin, and gather what little remains. I shall also go to my guild there and get some new spells. For soon I shall be able to use them!<br>
   On my way, for the sun shines, and I have to pass through Kithicor Forest on my way to the West Commons so that I may use the boat in freeport to venture on, no matter WHAT the odds against me are. Here begger have a small sum of coin for the day I meet with my brother again is near! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/bvoiceofthedragon.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sonjaleah>Sonjaleah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Goddess of Scale</span><br>  Posts: 195<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(12/31/02 7:29:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/fvoiceofthedragonfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: On the trail I continue</span><hr size=1> Sitting in on the cold snow I wait - peering questioningly at Peraspera.  Having awoke from a fitful sleep and being scared to death upon finding him in my bed - I followed him here.  Watching him - protecting him.<br>
<br>
Why do I do this? I have many things to do.  Dragons to protect.  Could it be they were right? the gods do not lie - but it can't be but I do feel a warming of my heart.<br>
<br>
Nooo alone is all I know.  Love pfft what is love.<br>
<br>
Lowering my eyelashes I inspect him - wondering if anyone will notice me slipping off to hide.  What did happen the other evening? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/bvoiceofthedragon.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whispurrwillowind>WhispurrWillowind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Green Snake</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(12/31/02 2:28:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/fvoiceofthedragonfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My Rescuer</span><hr size=1> Sitting in the dark corner of this run-down establishment, wiping my weapon of the blood of walruses we slaughtered later in the day and nursing a stale draft, I see Him at the bar.  Alone is he, slumped over numerous empty glasses of unknown libation.  He looks sad though I have seen him slay with tremendous courage so many foes, he now looks so vulnerable, so exposed.<br>
<br>
Hesitantly, I approach Him, not knowing what to say.  I notice his armour looks scorched from one of my blasts and I lower my head in discuss at my inability to be more accurate in my DD.  Still groggy from the intake of ale, I slowly reach the empty stool next to him and sit silently while he chews on batwing crunchies.  I reach out to one of his rough but gentle hands and gently squeeze it to show that I care and that I am sorry for the burns.  Our eyes meet.  He looks so tired…so alone. I’m alone… My heart misses a beat.  He smiles…<br>
<br>
“Bartender, another cold one”…(alcohol tolerance 6)!<br>
